<p>The VW debacle is apropos: at the very least, if you short stock and can't buy it when the time comes, expect to be bankrupt. </p>

<p>And the reason tranching is a problem here is that "safer" is relative, and is only meaningful if any of the investments are safe. Shooting yourself with a BB gun may be "safer" than doing so with a .38, but that doesn't mean either is remotely safe. (And both can void your life insurance.) I could argue, correctly, that my pet cat is smarter than a ballpoint pen: that doesn't make him smart by most standards.</p>

